 The Police Command in the Federal Capital Territory has relaxed its earlier announced movement restriction during the February 12 Area Councils elections in the territory. The Police Public Relations Officer in the FCT, DSP Josephine Adeh made this known in a statement on Friday in Abuja. She called on FCT residents to go about their normal legitimate business without the fear of harassment or molestation of any kind. Adeh pledged the commitment of the command to provide watertight security before, during and after the election. She urged members of the public to go out in their numbers to vote for candidates of their choice. Adeh enjoined residents to remain vigilant and report any suspicious or abnormal occurrence to the Police through 08032003913, 08061581938, 07057337653 and 08028940883. (NAN) 